'''Eloísa Díaz Insunza''' (June 25, 1866 &ndash; November 1, 1950), was the first female [[Medical school#Medical students|medical student]] to attend the [[University of Chile]], and the first woman to become a doctor in [[Chile]] as well as the entire continent of [[South America]].<ref name="nuestro">{{Cite web
